otilapia|flaviijosephi]]\n[[Category:Fish described in 1883]]\n[[Category:Cichlid fish of Asia]]\n[[Category:Fish of Israel]]\n[[Category:Fish of Syria]]\n[[Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot]]\n", "name_user": "37.202.124.171", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(Fixed content.)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Astatotilapia_flaviijosephi"}
{"title_page": "Secretariat for the Economy", "text_new": "{{about|the dicastery of the Roman Curia|the Mexican Ministry of Economy|Secretariat of Economy}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2014}}\n{{Roman Curia sidebar}}\n{{Politics of Vatican City}}\nThe '''Secretariat for the Economy''' ({{lang-it|Segreteria per l'economia}}) is a [[dicastery]] of the [[Roman Curia]] with authority over all economic activities of the [[Holy See]] and the [[Vatican City State]].<ref name=\"vis\">{{cite web | url=http://visnews-en.blogspot.co.at/2014/02/new-coordination-structure-for-economic.html | title=New Coordination Structure for the Economic and Administrative Affairs of the Holy See and Vatican City State | publisher=Holy See Press Office | date=24 February 2014 | accessdate=24 February 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Description==\n[[Pope Francis]] established the secretariat in a ''[[motu proprio]]'', ''Fidelis dispensator et prudens'', published on 24 February 2014. It is headed by a [[prefect]]\u2013originally a cardinal\u2013who reports directly to the Pope.<ref name=pellfirst>{{cite news|last=Reese|first=Thomas|title=Cardinal Pell is new Vatican financial watchdog |url=http://ncronline.org/blogs/ncr-today/cardinal-pell-new-vatican-financial-watchdog|accessdate=25 February 2014 |newspaper=National Catholic Reporter|date=24 February 2014}}</ref> It is, after the [[Secretariat of State (Holy See)|Secretariat of State]], the second dicastery named a ''secretariat'', an indication of its importance relative to other parts of the Curia.<ref name=crafty>{{cite news|last=Allen Jr.|first=John L.|title=Financial reform shows crafty political side of pope|url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/news/world/2014/02/25/financial-reform-shows-crafty-political-side-pope/PeipxfhuftqKNvUIGO7mKK/story.html|accessdate=25 February 2014|newspaper=Boston Globe|date=25 February 2014}}</ref> The seat of the secretariat is in [[Saint John's Tower (Vatican City)|Saint John's Tower]] in the [[Vatican Gardens]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.mondayvatican.com/pope-francis/pope-francis-observes-judges-and-acts-and-begins-establishing-a-parallel-curia | title=Pope Francis observes, judges, and acts. And begins establishing a parallel Curia | publisher=MondayVatican | date=3 March 2014 | accessdate=3 March 2014 | author=Andrea Gagliarducci}}</ref>\n\nCardinal [[George Pell]], [[Catholic Bishops and Archbishops of Sydney|Archbishop of Sydney]], was named the secretariat's first Prefect and \"asked to start work as soon as possible\".<ref name=head>{{cite web | url=http://www.news.va/en/news/australian-cardinal-to-head-new-vatican-secretaria | title=Australian Cardinal to head new Vatican Secretariat for Economy | work=News.va | date=24 February 2014 | accessdate=24 February 2014}}</ref> Pell said he would begin work at the Vatican \"by the end of March.\"<ref>{{cite news|last=Rocca|first=Francis X.|title=Pope establishes panel, with lay members, to oversee Vatican finances|url=http://www.catholicnews.com/data/stories/cns/1400772.htm|archive-url=http://webarchive.loc.gov/all/20150109225834/http://www.catholicnews.com/data/stories/cns/1400772.htm|url-status=dead|archive-date=9 January 2015|accessdate=25 February 2014|newspaper=Catholic News Service|date=24 February 2014}}</ref> The Pope also announced the formation of a ''Council for the Economy'' to set policy guidelines for the secretariat and analyze its work. The council comprises eight cardinals or bishops and seven lay persons \"with strong professional financial experience,\" chosen so that the body represents the global church. These members were named on 8 March.<ref name=head/><ref>{{cite press release | accessdate = 28 February 2019 | date= 8 March 2014 | url = http://press.vatican.va/content/salastampa/it/bollettino/pubblico/2014/03/08/0171/00366.html | publisher = Holy See Press Office | language = it | title = Commento al Comunicato sulla Nomina dei Membri del Comnsiglio per l\u2019Economia del Derettore della Sala Stampa, Rev.Do P. Federico Lombardi, S.I., 08.03.2014}}</ref> The council was headed by a Cardinal [[Reinhard Marx]] as coordinator.<ref name=\"motu proprio\">{{cite web|url=http://www.vis.va/vissolr/index.php?vi=all&dl=1ad89c78-6719-1176-bf48-530c5b262d10&dl_t=text/xml&dl_a=y&ul=1&ev=1|title=Motu proprio \"Fidelis dispensator et prudens\" for the Management of the Economic Assets of the Holy See|publisher=Vatican Information Service|accessdate=26 February 2014|url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140302120043/http://www.vis.va/vissolr/index.php?vi=all&dl=1ad89c78-6719-1176-bf48-530c5b262d10&dl_t=text%2Fxml&dl_a=y&ul=1&ev=1|archivedate=2 March 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 5 June 2015, [[Pope Francis]] appointed [[Libero Milone]] as [[Auditor General]].<ref name=\"motu proprio\"/><ref>{{cite press release |language=it |accessdate = 28 February 2019|publisher = Holy See Press Office | url = http://press.vatican.va/content/salastampa/it/bollettino/pubblico/2015/06/05/0429/00937.html | title= Rinunce e nomine, 05.06.2015 }}</ref>\n\nA meeting of the Council for the Economy was held in September 2014 to discuss the statutes of the new secretariat. The Council also discussed the transfer of responsibilities from the [[Administration of the Patrimony of the Apostolic See]] to the Secretariat for the Economy and the criteria for establishing a budgeting system.<ref>{{cite news| date= 5 September 2014 | accessdate=28 February 2019| url= https://zenit.org/articles/meeting-of-vatican-council-for-the-economy-ends/ |work=Zenit| title= Meeting of Vatican Council for the Economy Ends }}</ref>\n\nOn 3 March, Pope Francis appointed Monsignor [[Alfred Xuereb]] as the first General Secretary of the Secretariat.<ref>{{cite news |last=Tornielli|first=Andrea|title=Francis appoints Fr. Xuereb as secretary general of the Vatican's new economy secretariat |url=http://vaticaninsider.lastampa.it/en/the-vatican/detail/articolo/xuereb-francesco-francisco-francis-32443/|accessdate=3 March 2014|newspaper=Vatican Insider|date=3 March 2014}}</ref> Xuereb later left this post in February 2018.<ref>{{cite news | work = La Stampa |accessdate = 28 February 2019 | url = http://www.lastampa.it/2018/02/23/vaticaninsider/two-new-nuncios-from-the-roman-curia-xuereb-leaves-the-secretariat-for-the-economy-jfigmIsNCSWOBsRIBb6OCI/pagina.html | date= 23 February 2018 | title = Two new nuncios from the Roman Curia, Xuereb leaves the Secretariat for the Economy| first=Andrea | last = Tornielli}}</ref> On 22 March, Pope Francis appointed Monsignor [[Brian Ferme]], an Australian-born jurist and head of the St. Pius X Faculty of Canon Law in Venice, as the first Prelate Secretary of the Council that oversees the Secretariat.<ref>{{cite web |author=Mickens, Robert |title=Vatican's New Finance Expert is a Man of Myster |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160913082724/http://www.globalpulsemagazine.com/news/vaticans-new-finance-expert-is-man-of-mystery/383 |accessdate=13 August 2016 |website=Global pulse magazine}}</ref> \n\nIn a ''motu proprio'' issued on 9 July 2014 the responsibilities of the Secretariat for the Economy were extended considerably, since it decreed that the Ordinary Section of the [[Administration of the Patrimony of the Apostolic See]] (APSA) is to be transferred to the Secretariat,<ref name=\"VIS 2014\">{{cite web | url=http://visnews-en.blogspot.co.at/2014/07/new-economic-framework-for-holy-see.html | title=New Economic Framework for the Holy See | publisher=Vatican Information Service | date=9 July 2014 | accessdate=13 July 2014}}</ref> giving the latter control over purchasing and human resources.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/news/world/2014/07/09/after-scandals-vatican-aims-model-finances/618G6hEsfKJKAG0iAvXbtM/story.html | title=After scandals, Vatican aims to be model on finances | publisher=Boston Globe | date=9 July 2014 | accessdate=13 July 2014 | author=[[John L. Allen, Jr.]]}}</ref> \n\nBoth the Secretariat and Council were given formal status in February 2015.<ref>[http://www.catholicnewsagency.com/news/cardinal-pells-vatican-economy-office-gets-new-statutes-54667/ Cardinal Pell's Vatican economy office gets new statutes]</ref>\n\n==Current Membership==\n*[[Luigi Misto]], Acting Prefect\n*[[Reinhard Marx]], Coordinator\n*[[Juan Luis Cipriani Thorne]], Member \n*[[Daniel DiNardo]], Member\n*[[Wilfrid Napier]], Member\n*[[Jean-Pierre Ricard]], Member\n*[[Norberto Rivera Carrera]], Member\n*[[John Tong Hon]], Member\n\n==Prefects==\n*[[George Pell]] (24 February 2014<ref name=pellfirst/> \u2013 24 February 2019),<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.catholicnewsagency.com/news/cardinal-pell-no-longer-prefect-of-vaticans-economy-secretariat-98982 | title=Cardinal Pell no longer prefect of Vatican's economy secretariat | publisher=Catholic News Agency | date=26 February 2019 | accessdate=27 February 2019}}</ref> on leave of absence from 29 June 2017<ref>{{cite press release | url=http://press.vatican.va/content/salastampa/it/bollettino/pubblico/2017/06/29/0459/01028.html | title=Comunicato della Sala Stampa della Santa Sede, 29.06.2017  | publisher=Vatican Press Office | date=29 June 2017 | accessdate=27 February 2019 |language=it }}</ref>\n*[[Juan Antonio Guerrero Alves]], [[Society of Jesus|SJ]], (appointed 14 November 2019, effective 1 January 2020<ref>{{cite press release |title=Rinunce e nomine, 14.11.2019 | date =14 November 2019 |url=https://press.vatican.va/content/salastampa/it/bollettino/pubblico/2019/11/14/0871/01821.html |publisher=Holy See Press Office |accessdate=14 November 2019}}</ref> \u2013 present)\n\n==See also==\n*[[Index of Vatican City-related articles]]\n\n==Sources==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Roman Curia footer}}\n{{Vatican City topics}}\n{{Holy See}}\n\n[[Category:2014 establishments in Vatican City]]\n[[Category:Economy of Vatican City]]\n[[Category:Government agencies established in 2014]]\n[[Category:Government of Vatican City]]\n[[Category:Dicasteries]]\n[[Category:Secretariats (Holy See)|Economy]]\n[[Category:Financial regulatory authorities]]\n", "text_old": "{{about|the dicastery of the Roman Curia|the Mexican Ministry of Economy|Secretariat of Economy}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2014}}\n{{Roman Curia sidebar}}\n{{Politics of Vatican City}}\nThe '''Secretariat for the Economy''' ({{lang-it|Segreteria per l'economia}}) is a [[dicastery]] of the [[Roman Curia]] with authority over all economic activities of the [[Holy See]] and the [[Vatican City State]].<ref name=\"vis\">{{cite web | url=http://visnews-en.blogspot.co.at/2014/02/new-coordination-structure-for-economic.html | title=New Coordination Structure for the Economic and Administrative Affairs of the Holy See and Vatican City State | publisher=Holy See Press Office | date=24 February 2014 | accessdate=24 February 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Description==\n[[Pope Francis]] established the secretariat in a ''[[motu proprio]]'', ''Fidelis dispensator et prudens'', published on 24 February 2014. It is headed by a [[prefect]]\u2013originally a cardinal\u2013who reports directly to the Pope.<ref name=pellfirst>{{cite news|last=Reese|first=Thomas|title=Cardinal Pell is new Vatican financial watchdog |url=http://ncronline.org/blogs/ncr-today/cardinal-pell-new-vatican-financial-watchdog|accessdate=25 February 2014 |newspaper=National Catholic Reporter|date=24 February 2014}}</ref> It is, after the [[Secretariat of State (Holy See)|Secretariat of State]], the second dicastery named a ''secretariat'', an indication of its importance relative to other parts of the Curia.<ref name=crafty>{{cite news|last=Allen Jr.|first=John L.|title=Financial reform shows crafty political side of pope|url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/news/world/2014/02/25/financial-reform-shows-crafty-political-side-pope/PeipxfhuftqKNvUIGO7mKK/story.html|accessdate=25 February 2014|newspaper=Boston Globe|date=25 February 2014}}</ref> The seat of the secretariat is in [[Saint John's Tower (Vatican City)|Saint John's Tower]] in the [[Vatican Gardens]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.mondayvatican.com/pope-francis/pope-francis-observes-judges-and-acts-and-begins-establishing-a-parallel-curia | title=Pope Francis observes, judges, and acts. And begins establishing a parallel Curia | publisher=MondayVatican | date=3 March 2014 | accessdate=3 March 2014 | author=Andrea Gagliarducci}}</ref>\n\nCardinal [[George Pell]], [[Catholic Bishops and Archbishops of Sydney|Archbishop of Sydney]], was named the secretariat's first Prefect and \"asked to start work as soon as possible\".<ref name=head>{{cite web | url=http://www.news.va/en/news/australian-cardinal-to-head-new-vatican-secretaria | title=Australian Cardinal to head new Vatican Secretariat for Economy | work=News.va | date=24 February 2014 | accessdate=24 February 2014}}</ref> Pell said he would begin work at the Vatican \"by the end of March.\"<ref>{{cite news|last=Rocca|first=Francis X.|title=Pope establishes panel, with lay members, to oversee Vatican finances|url=http://www.catholicnews.com/data/stories/cns/1400772.htm|archive-url=http://webarchive.loc.gov/all/20150109225834/http://www.catholicnews.com/data/stories/cns/1400772.htm|url-status=dead|archive-date=9 January 2015|accessdate=25 February 2014|newspaper=Catholic News Service|date=24 February 2014}}</ref> The Pope also announced the formation of a ''Council for the Economy'' to set policy guidelines for the secretariat and analyze its work. The council comprises eight cardinals or bishops and seven lay persons \"with strong professional financial experience,\" chosen so that the body represents the global church. These members were named on 8 March.<ref name=head/><ref>{{cite press release | accessdate = 28 February 2019 | date= 8 March 2014 | url = http://press.vatican.va/content/salastampa/it/bollettino/pubblico/2014/03/08/0171/00366.html | publisher = Holy See Press Office | language = it | title = Commento al Comunicato sulla Nomina dei Membri del Comnsiglio per l\u2019Economia del Derettore della Sala Stampa, Rev.Do P. Federico Lombardi, S.I., 08.03.2014}}</ref> The council was headed by a Cardinal [[Reinhard Marx]] as coordinator.<ref name=\"motu proprio\">{{cite web|url=http://www.vis.va/vissolr/index.php?vi=all&dl=1ad89c78-6719-1176-bf48-530c5b262d10&dl_t=text/xml&dl_a=y&ul=1&ev=1|title=Motu proprio \"Fidelis dispensator et prudens\" for the Management of the Economic Assets of the Holy See|publisher=Vatican Information Service|accessdate=26 February 2014|url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140302120043/http://www.vis.va/vissolr/index.php?vi=all&dl=1ad89c78-6719-1176-bf48-530c5b262d10&dl_t=text%2Fxml&dl_a=y&ul=1&ev=1|archivedate=2 March 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref> On 5 June 2015, [[Pope Francis]] appointed [[Libero Milone]] as [[Auditor General]].<ref name=\"motu proprio\"/><ref>{{cite press release |language=it |accessdate = 28 February 2019|publisher = Holy See Press Office | url = http://press.vatican.va/content/salastampa/it/bollettino/pubblico/2015/06/05/0429/00937.html | title= Rinunce e nomine, 05.06.2015 }}</ref>\n\nA meeting of the Council for the Economy was held in September 2014 to discuss the statutes of the new secretariat. The Council also discussed the transfer of responsibilities from the [[Administration of the Patrimony of the Apostolic See]] to the Secretariat for the Economy and the criteria for establishing a budgeting system.<ref>{{cite news| date= 5 September 2014 | accessdate=28 February 2019| url= https://zenit.org/articles/meeting-of-vatican-council-for-the-economy-ends/ |work=Zenit| title= Meeting of Vatican Council for the Economy Ends }}</ref>\n\nOn 3 March, Pope Francis appointed Monsignor [[Alfred Xuereb]] as the first General Secretary of the Secretariat.<ref>{{cite news |last=Tornielli|first=Andrea|title=Francis appoints Fr. Xuereb as secretary general of the Vatican's new economy secretariat |url=http://vaticaninsider.lastampa.it/en/the-vatican/detail/articolo/xuereb-francesco-francisco-francis-32443/|accessdate=3 March 2014|newspaper=Vatican Insider|date=3 March 2014}}</ref> Xuereb later left this post in February 2018.<ref>{{cite news | work = La Stampa |accessdate = 28 February 2019 | url = http://www.lastampa.it/2018/02/23/vaticaninsider/two-new-nuncios-from-the-roman-curia-xuereb-leaves-the-secretariat-for-the-economy-jfigmIsNCSWOBsRIBb6OCI/pagina.html | date= 23 February 2018 | title = Two new nuncios from the Roman Curia, Xuereb leaves the Secretariat for the Economy| first=Andrea | last = Tornielli}}</ref> On 22 March, Pope Francis appointed Monsignor [[Brian Ferme]], an Australian-born jurist and head of the St. Pius X Faculty of Canon Law in Venice, as the first Prelate Secretary of the Council that oversees the Secretariat.<ref>{{cite web |author=Mickens, Robert |title=Vatican's New Finance Expert is a Man of Myster |url=http://www.globalpulsemagazine.com/news/vaticans-new-finance-expert-is-man-of-mystery/383 |accessdate=13 August 2016 |website=Global pulse magazine}}</ref>\n\nIn a ''motu proprio'' issued on 9 July 2014 the responsibilities of the Secretariat for the Economy were extended considerably, since it decreed that the Ordinary Section of the [[Administration of the Patrimony of the Apostolic See]] (APSA) is to be transferred to the Secretariat,<ref name=\"VIS 2014\">{{cite web | url=http://visnews-en.blogspot.co.at/2014/07/new-economic-framework-for-holy-see.html | title=New Economic Framework for the Holy See | publisher=Vatican Information Service | date=9 July 2014 | accessdate=13 July 2014}}</ref> giving the latter control over purchasing and human resources.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/news/world/2014/07/09/after-scandals-vatican-aims-model-finances/618G6hEsfKJKAG0iAvXbtM/story.html | title=After scandals, Vatican aims to be model on finances | publisher=Boston Globe | date=9 July 2014 | accessdate=13 July 2014 | author=[[John L. Allen, Jr.]]}}</ref> \n\nBoth the Secretariat and Council were given formal status in February 2015.<ref>[http://www.catholicnewsagency.com/news/cardinal-pells-vatican-economy-office-gets-new-statutes-54667/ Cardinal Pell's Vatican economy office gets new statutes]</ref>\n\n==Current Membership==\n*[[Luigi Misto]], Acting Prefect\n*[[Reinhard Marx]], Coordinator\n*[[Juan Luis Cipriani Thorne]], Member \n*[[Daniel DiNardo]], Member\n*[[Wilfrid Napier]], Member\n*[[Jean-Pierre Ricard]], Member\n*[[Norberto Rivera Carrera]], Member\n*[[John Tong Hon]], Member\n\n==Prefects==\n*[[George Pell]] (24 February 2014<ref name=pellfirst/> \u2013 24 February 2019),<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.catholicnewsagency.com/news/cardinal-pell-no-longer-prefect-of-vaticans-economy-secretariat-98982 | title=Cardinal Pell no longer prefect of Vatican's economy secretariat | publisher=Catholic News Agency | date=26 February 2019 | accessdate=27 February 2019}}</ref> on leave of absence from 29 June 2017<ref>{{cite press release | url=http://press.vatican.va/content/salastampa/it/bollettino/pubblico/2017/06/29/0459/01028.html | title=Comunicato della Sala Stampa della Santa Sede, 29.06.2017  | publisher=Vatican Press Office | date=29 June 2017 | accessdate=27 February 2019 |language=it }}</ref>\n*[[Juan Antonio Guerrero Alves]], [[Society of Jesus|SJ]], (appointed 14 November 2019, effective 1 January 2020<ref>{{cite press release |title=Rinunce e nomine, 14.11.2019 | date =14 November 2019 |url=https://press.vatican.va/content/salastampa/it/bollettino/pubblico/2019/11/14/0871/01821.html |publisher=Holy See Press Office |accessdate=14 November 2019}}</ref> \u2013 present)\n\n==See also==\n*[[Index of Vatican City-related articles]]\n\n==Sources==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Roman Curia footer}}\n{{Vatican City topics}}\n{{Holy See}}\n\n[[Category:2014 establishments in Vatican City]]\n[[Category:Economy of Vatican City]]\n[[Category:Government agencies established in 2014]]\n[[Category:Government of Vatican City]]\n[[Category:Dicasteries]]\n[[Category:S